::Prowl::

Prowl frowns at Iris, thankful for Iron Raptor's defence of him. He 
was trying to find something to think of that didn't get him excited 
or nervous, but nothing worked. Maximal victory, exited, relaxing 
with Iron Raptor, excited, a nice battle, excited, what he was about 
to do, nervious.

He frowns at Iris' exclamation, looking at the cracked screen and 
glancing at a nice stream they were passing. He had a sudden urge 
to 'accidently' drop Iris in, but he knew that she was probably right.

He sighs, relaxing on Iron Raptor, his mind dwelling on dropping Iris 
into the stream. It was a stupid thing to think of, but nervious 
minds often think of stupid things.

A small smile plays across Prowl's lips as he thinks of Iris floating 
downstream and screaming obsenities at him and Iron Raptor, the 
Maximal relaxing. Finally getting his mind off of what lay ahead, his 
sparkbeat relaxing along with his mind.
